\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces Controlled torus inverse benchmark rendered directly from the dense VTU export of the canonical run. The left panel shows the prescribed deformed configuration colored by displacement magnitude, and the right panel shows the boundary traction-error magnitude on the same geometry and camera. Because the kinematics are prescribed, these panels should be read as diagnostics of the observation fit rather than as evidence of a learned displacement field. The main conclusion is that the traction mismatch remains small and spatially localized over the observed boundary surface.\relax }}{25}{figure.caption.45}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:torus_inverse_original_fields}{{11}{25}{Controlled torus inverse benchmark rendered directly from the dense VTU export of the canonical run. The left panel shows the prescribed deformed configuration colored by displacement magnitude, and the right panel shows the boundary traction-error magnitude on the same geometry and camera. Because the kinematics are prescribed, these panels should be read as diagnostics of the observation fit rather than as evidence of a learned displacement field. The main conclusion is that the traction mismatch remains small and spatially localized over the observed boundary surface.\relax }{figure.caption.45}{}}
